    <h1 class="title is-3 is-color-primary mt-6">
      About INNOSERV
    </h1>
    <h2 class="subtitle is-4 mt-3">
      INNOSERV is a project developing an EU wide research agenda to evaluate innovation in the field of social
      services (especially for health, education and welfare services). 
      This will help define future research activities.
    </h2>
    <div class="content is-size-4">
        INNOSERV responds to the FP7-Cooperation call FP7-SSH-2011-3 for a ‘support action concerning a social platform on innovative social services.’
        Answering the objectives of the call, the INNOSERV project will:
        <ul class="is-size-5">
          <li>Produce short visual examples combined with theoretical case studies of ‘innovative’ practices in the fields of health, education and welfare. These will be used to help inform discussion and debate;</li>
          <li>Develop a web based ‘social platform’ for continuing dialogue;</li>
          <li>Manage a multi-level discussion involving a wide range of stakeholders from research, policy making and practice communities in the EU to identify priorities for future research and development.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

